21/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A bilateral agreement on easing the EU visa regime for BiH citizens must be sealed in March, according to BiH Security Ministry Secretary Bakir Dautbasic. The country's chief negotiator in the talks on visa relieving and readmission with the EU briefed reporters Wednesday (December 20th), after the first meeting between negotiation teams in Brussels. 
Also Wednesday, BiH and France sealed a bilateral agreement on readmission of illegal migrants. According to BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak, Sarajevo and France are preparing to sign another key accord, this time on political co-operation. (Nezavisne novine - 21/12/06; PBS BiH, RTRS - 20/12/06)
